1
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:20,041
[thudding footsteps]

2
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:26,500
[FEMALE FAIRY]
Over here! Hurry up!

3
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:28,291
Don't be such a wimp!

4
00:00:28,375 --> 00:00:29,875
[ARATA]
Hold on.

5
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:32,208
[FEMALE FAIRY] We're going
to have to leave you behind!

6
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:33,791
You're so slow!

7
00:00:33,875 --> 00:00:35,416
[ARATA]
Can't you slow down a bit?

8
00:00:36,416 --> 00:00:38,291
Some of us don't have wings.

9
00:00:38,375 --> 00:00:40,208
Oh, is that them?

10
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,750
Uh, hi. How are you?

11
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:46,083
I'm here from the Shinjuku Ward.

12
00:00:46,166 --> 00:00:47,416
[ANOTHER grumbles]

13
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:48,750
[ARATA]
Haven't seen you before.

14
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:50,916
Where are you from?
What's your name?

15
00:00:53,250 --> 00:00:55,916
My name. Good question.

16
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,666
Let me think. What's my name?

17
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:02,625
Sorry, I can't remember
who I am.

18
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:40,875
[KYOICHI] An Another
that suffers from amnesia?

19
00:02:40,958 --> 00:02:43,541
Strange. Not sure
why you brought him here.

20
00:02:43,625 --> 00:02:47,125
Well, I wanted your opinion
on his condition.

21
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,625
You can't just
bring them here, though.

22
00:02:49,708 --> 00:02:51,250
I didn't think. Sorry.

23
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:54,458
I can't walk away
and leave it behind.

24
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:57,125
Though it's been shattered,
broken to pieces.

25
00:02:57,208 --> 00:03:00,250
My beautiful home is gone,
now I have nothing.

26
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:03,583
Um, he's saying that the statue
where he's been living

27
00:03:03,666 --> 00:03:06,375
has been destroyed,
but he still can't leave it.

28
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:09,416
Some Anothers require
a kind of home vessel

29
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,875
-to host their spirit.
-A vessel?

30
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,750
Oh, man,
that's gotta be rough,

31
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,333
losing your home,
then not being able

32
00:03:15,416 --> 00:03:16,666
to remember who you are.

33
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:18,208
[THEO]
This is pointless!

34
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:20,250
-I'm getting absolutely nowhere!
-Here we go again.

35
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,541
Do you think this means
he wants to have a meeting?

36
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:25,541
All I can tell
from a piece this size

37
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:27,291
is that it's from
a very old statue.

38
00:03:27,375 --> 00:03:30,166
And our equipment
isn't very much help.

39
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:33,333
I'll send a sample of it
to the university for analysis.

40
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:34,875
[SENDA]
That seems complicated.

41
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:36,916
I just wish we knew his name.

42
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,333
Fine. I hear what you're saying.

43
00:03:39,416 --> 00:03:41,666
I'll go see if I can find out
his name and type.

44
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,000
[sighs]

45
00:03:45,541 --> 00:03:46,791
I'd send Kyoichi with you,

46
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:48,583
but he's gotta go
help his sister.

47
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:51,333
Oh, uh, right.
Today's the big day.

48
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:53,916
She's finalizing
her post-graduation plans.

49
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,166
Huh? Nice. Congrats.

50
00:03:56,250 --> 00:03:59,375
By the way, I'm a little behind
updating the database

51
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:00,833
with all this new information.

52
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:03,416
I'll do it. I'm the one
who brought him here.

53
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:04,875
Didn't mean to throw you off.

54
00:04:04,958 --> 00:04:06,875
Sure you can handle that?

55
00:04:06,958 --> 00:04:08,833
-[ARATA] Yep.
-That works for me.

56
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,708
Trust him. He'll be fine.

57
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,250
Uh...

58
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,750
Hey, If you're good, I'm good.

59
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:18,041
Good luck. You've got your work
cut out for you.

60
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:19,500
[ARATA]
Right. I won't let you down.

61
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:21,750
[knocking on door]

62
00:04:23,416 --> 00:04:25,958
Huh? Are you okay?

63
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:27,791
[ANOTHER]
Hmm? Mm.

64
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:32,083
I'm not sure. Need food.

65
00:04:32,166 --> 00:04:34,500
Oh! Of course you do.

66
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:36,375
Anything in particular
you'd like to eat?

67
00:04:36,458 --> 00:04:39,458
In particular to eat?

68
00:04:39,541 --> 00:04:41,666
What's in particular?

69
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:44,333
[ARATA] I mean, what's your
favorite thing to eat?

70
00:04:44,416 --> 00:04:47,625
I do love honey.
Do you have honey?

71
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:49,625
But will that be enough?

72
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:52,375
-Yes. Please.
-I can do that!

73
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:55,500
♪

74
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:58,583
Here you go.
How do you like to eat it?

75
00:04:58,666 --> 00:04:59,750
On bread or what?

76
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:01,416
[ANOTHER]
Hmm.

77
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,041
[ANOTHER grunting]

78
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:06,666
Uh, I'll do it.

79
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,875
Or not.

80
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:14,625
Wait!
You don't wanna do that!

81
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,166
-[ANOTHER] Oh!
-[bottle clinking]

82
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,750
-[muffled grunting]
-[ARATA] Aah!

83
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,916
Hang on!
I'll look for some napkins!

84
00:05:22,625 --> 00:05:23,791
[sighs]

85
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,541
Rough night there, buddy?

86
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:29,583
Yeah, you could say that.

87
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:31,375
I forgot to tell you.

88
00:05:31,458 --> 00:05:32,583
If he's the type of Another

89
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:34,166
that requires
some kind of vessel,

90
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,708
-that could get complicated.
-How so?

91
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,500
[THEO]
For one, without a vessel,

92
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,041
he has nowhere to go.

93
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:41,958
-Oh.
-But don't worry.

94
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:43,375
There is a solution.

95
00:05:43,458 --> 00:05:45,458
He'll be fine if we give him
a place to stay.

96
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,541
-Where though?
-[THEO] You got this.

97
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:51,625
Uh... Huh?

98
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:53,208
[ARATA yells]

99
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,708
[sighs]

100
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:59,000
[ARATA]
It'll be fine.

101
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:01,166
I can take him home
just for today.

102
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:04,750
♪

103
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:05,958
Who's this guy?

104
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:06,958
Well?

105
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:08,208
Huh?

106
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:10,208
Oh. He, uh...

107
00:06:10,291 --> 00:06:11,791
[YUKI]
He smells like a bear!

108
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:13,958
Why would you bring someone
in here who smells so bad?

109
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,958
Why does that
upset you so much?

110
00:06:16,041 --> 00:06:18,166
He's spreading his divine aura
all over the place

111
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:19,666
and not even trying
to hide it!

112
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:20,791
[YUKI]
He can't stay here

113
00:06:20,875 --> 00:06:22,250
unless you want me to go crazy!

114
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:24,875
Guys, this is all
just part of my job.

115
00:06:24,958 --> 00:06:27,833
[YUKI] Fine, then I'll leave!
I'm outta here!

116
00:06:27,916 --> 00:06:30,041
Wait for me, Yuki.
I'll come with you!

117
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:31,000
Hey, guys!

118
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,041
[groans]

119
00:06:34,041 --> 00:06:36,541
[school bell rings]

120
00:06:36,625 --> 00:06:37,541
[MALE TEACHER]
Hmm.

121
00:06:37,625 --> 00:06:39,375
Tell me something, Mr. Sakaki.

122
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:41,166
What are your thoughts
on your little sister's

123
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:43,083
current post-graduation plans?

124
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:45,458
Uh! Um, Well, I,

125
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:48,333
I love my big sister,
and little sister,

126
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:50,208
and I honestly just
want her to be happy.

127
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:51,416
But I think she should...

128
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:54,375
He's a little nervous
today, sir.

129
00:06:54,458 --> 00:06:56,833
I'm sorry.
Takes him a sec to warm up.

130
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:59,000
-Kyoichi?
-Uh, she's right.

131
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:02,250
Just a reminder, no need
to be nervous, just relax.

132
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:10,291
-[alarm rings]
-[ARATA groaning]

133
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:14,000
[moans]

134
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:18,625
[ANOTHER grunts softly]

135
00:07:18,708 --> 00:07:19,791
[ARATA]
Uh...

136
00:07:26,791 --> 00:07:28,333
Here's breakfast.

137
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:30,208
Try not to spill it
this time, 'kay?

138
00:07:30,291 --> 00:07:31,791
[ANOTHER]
Hmm.

139
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:33,083
-[lid pops]
-Uh...

140
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,500
So, I was thinking
we could find you

141
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:42,833
a new place to live today?

142
00:07:42,916 --> 00:07:43,958
[ANOTHER]
Hmm.

143
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:47,708
[ARATA]
I'll even throw this in. Deal?

144
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:49,666
Hell no! He smells!

145
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,291
You think that's enough
for us to take him in?

146
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:53,291
[FEMALE FAIRY]
Go insult someone else!

147
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:54,875
[MALE FAIRY]
Yeah, get out of here!

148
00:07:54,958 --> 00:07:56,125
Then, what should I do?

149
00:07:56,208 --> 00:07:57,833
[MALE FAIRY]
You can start by leaving!

150
00:07:57,916 --> 00:08:00,125
♪

151
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:02,125
[ARATA snoring]

152
00:08:02,208 --> 00:08:04,750
♪

153
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,250
[alarm ringing]

154
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,541
[moaning]

155
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:13,166
♪

156
00:08:28,416 --> 00:08:29,291
[ANOTHER]
Hmm?

157
00:08:30,291 --> 00:08:31,541
[groans]

158
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:37,000
[inaudible dialogue]

159
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:44,083
♪

160
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:09,166
[inaudible dilaogue]

161
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:14,250
[alarm ringing]

162
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,291
[ARATA moans softly]

163
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:19,125
[ringing continues]

164
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:21,625
[ringing stops]

165
00:09:25,791 --> 00:09:27,375
Hmm, hmm?

166
00:09:32,166 --> 00:09:35,625
♪

167
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,250
[KYOICHI] Maybe it's just me,
but it seems like

168
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,500
that Another's doing
a lot better.

169
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,125
[THEO]
What about that one over there?

170
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:44,083
[gulping]

171
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:46,125
Are you gonna be
all right, Arata?

172
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:48,125
-You tired?
-Sure.

173
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:49,875
Been walking for days on end.

174
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:51,416
I didn't know it'd be like this.

175
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,916
Damn right. Believe me,
I know how you feel.

176
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,875
I'm sure you do.
I shouldn't complain.

177
00:09:57,958 --> 00:09:59,541
Hunting for clues is my job,

178
00:09:59,625 --> 00:10:01,791
and the wear and tear
is just part of the package.

179
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:05,208
With that, I'm off
to find this guy a home.

180
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:09,041
[ARATA]
Finished eating?

181
00:10:09,125 --> 00:10:12,000
Why don't we check out places
in this neighborhood today?

182
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:14,791
♪

183
00:10:20,625 --> 00:10:23,375
[ARATA]
A new home, huh?

184
00:10:23,458 --> 00:10:26,083
But what kind of place
would be good for him?

185
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:28,041
Uh. Oh, no. He's gone!

186
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:33,166
Okay, there he is.
Thank goodness.

187
00:10:33,250 --> 00:10:36,500
♪

188
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:43,000
[ANOTHER]
Hmm.

189
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:45,166
I like the atmosphere
of this one.

190
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:47,791
I believe it will be
a very worthy home for me.

191
00:10:47,875 --> 00:10:50,291
Hold on! I think
we'd better keep looking!

192
00:10:50,375 --> 00:10:51,791
-[KIO GONGEN] Hey!
-[ARATA gasps]

193
00:10:51,875 --> 00:10:55,416
Who gave you permission
to set foot on my property?

194
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,500
Consider this an honor.

195
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:59,083
I've decided to make this place

196
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:00,958
you call yours
my temporary home.

197
00:11:01,041 --> 00:11:04,041
Temporary home?
How dare you?

198
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,541
Though, I suppose
I should expect

199
00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:07,708
this kind of entitled behavior
from a hunting god!

200
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:09,166
What did you say?

201
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,125
Listen! Let's take a step back!

202
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:13,458
Seimei! What are you doing here
with this trash?

203
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:14,625
Helping him.

204
00:11:14,708 --> 00:11:16,083
He lost his vessel and memories,

205
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:17,208
and he's having a rough time!

206
00:11:17,291 --> 00:11:18,208
[KIO GONGEN scoffs]

207
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:19,666
Not my problem, is it?

208
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:21,750
Get those bear fleas
out of here, Seimei!

209
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:24,166
And don't you dare come back!

210
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,125
[ANOTHER]
Hmm.

211
00:11:25,208 --> 00:11:26,833
[sighs]
Let's go.

212
00:11:26,916 --> 00:11:30,333
In general, shrines will already
be occupied by gods.

213
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:32,416
But there is such
a strong power here.

214
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,916
-Not easy to give up.
-You have to.

215
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,208
It's not worth starting
a battle over, is it?

216
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:39,916
If you can't find a vessel
that isn't occupied,

217
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,750
you leave me no choice
but to do battle

218
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:43,250
for my right to stay here.

219
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:44,791
Uh, please don't go in there.

220
00:11:44,875 --> 00:11:47,000
I promise you'll regret it!
[groans]

221
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:51,083
Hey, kid, what's wrong?
Come on, wake up!

222
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:52,333
Please!

223
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:58,750
Oh. Hi.

224
00:11:58,833 --> 00:11:59,916
Hi.

225
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,625
Rise and shine, sleeping beauty.

226
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:05,166
You owe this guy your thanks.

227
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:08,125
Pretty amazing that Another
brought you back to us.

228
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,125
You really need to take
better care of yourself.

229
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:14,875
I appreciate your work ethic,
but you're pushing way too hard.

230
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,041
I apologize.

231
00:12:16,125 --> 00:12:17,750
There's more
to it than just that.

232
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:21,166
Arata's lifeforce is slowly
being siphoned from his body.

233
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,500
That's the reason he collapsed.

234
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:24,541
Does that have anything
to do with the fact

235
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:26,458
that this guy's starting
to regain his strength?

236
00:12:26,541 --> 00:12:27,791
[warbling]

237
00:12:27,875 --> 00:12:30,125
That surprised him,
which could only mean

238
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:32,333
that he didn't do it
on purpose.

239
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:34,416
Can he drain energy
just by being close?

240
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:35,708
No.

241
00:12:35,791 --> 00:12:37,291
It's more likely
that he's absorbing

242
00:12:37,375 --> 00:12:38,583
the energy humans are spending

243
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:40,875
whenever their curiosity
focuses on him.

244
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:49,708
-Where are you going?
-Leaving, of course.

245
00:12:49,791 --> 00:12:52,250
Since I'm responsible
for draining your lifeforce,

246
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:53,541
the last thing I want to do

247
00:12:53,625 --> 00:12:55,041
is remain here
and cause your death!

248
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,791
You still need a home!

249
00:12:56,875 --> 00:12:59,583
And we haven't figured out
your name yet, either!

250
00:12:59,666 --> 00:13:01,625
My pride is important to me.

251
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:03,375
Respect that. Please.

252
00:13:03,458 --> 00:13:05,583
I will not steal the life
of an innocent man,

253
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:08,166
especially not when that man
has done so much for me.

254
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:10,166
But you'll make
my work more difficult!

255
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:12,500
I'm not done yet!

256
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:15,083
It's still my job
to figure out who you are!

257
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:17,125
That means
you're not allowed to leave!

258
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,208
Aren't you afraid
of what could happen?

259
00:13:20,291 --> 00:13:22,500
[ARATA] We've been together
this whole time,

260
00:13:22,583 --> 00:13:24,375
and I'm not dead.

261
00:13:24,458 --> 00:13:26,375
[sighs]
That's true.

262
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:29,125
[THEO] Ya know, I'd apologize
for killing the moment,

263
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:31,916
except I have no idea
what's being said here.

264
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:32,875
[KYOICHI]
Translate, please.

265
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:34,208
Right, I keep forgetting.

266
00:13:34,291 --> 00:13:35,833
Forgive me.

267
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:40,333
Interesting twist.
Theo? Your thoughts?

268
00:13:40,416 --> 00:13:42,208
I just need his name.

269
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:45,250
Once we know that, everything
else will fall right into place.

270
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,875
I agree, then let's keep
moving forward.

271
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:49,583
I'll stay with the Another.

272
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:52,000
Maybe he'll say something that
will be a clue as to who he is.

273
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:55,208
For real? Did you forget
that you just collapsed?

274
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:56,500
[ARATA]
I'm fine.

275
00:13:56,583 --> 00:13:58,750
At least we know
it's not because I'm sick.

276
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:01,625
Look, I know what I'm doing,
all right? I've got this.

277
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:06,791
Also, I realize I may have lost
some of my strength,

278
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:08,833
but that Another is feeling
a whole lot better

279
00:14:08,916 --> 00:14:09,875
because of me.

280
00:14:09,958 --> 00:14:11,041
I'd call that progress.

281
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:13,708
I'd call you
a very stubborn guy.

282
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,166
Excellent work.

283
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:19,291
[gasps]
What did you say?

284
00:14:19,375 --> 00:14:21,041
[KYOICHI] Never hurts
to be supportive, Theo.

285
00:14:22,041 --> 00:14:23,666
Besides, we hired him,
didn't we?

286
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,458
Can't fault him
for making us look good.

287
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:29,708
Yeah, I guess you're right.
Just keep me updated, please.

288
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:30,791
I will!

289
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:33,833
[ANOTHER]
Hmm.

290
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,000
[beeps]

291
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:45,875
♪

292
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,750
[WOMAN]
Thank you! Have a nice day!

293
00:14:57,416 --> 00:15:00,333
♪

294
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,708
What's the matter?

295
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:06,833
The number of people here.

296
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:08,583
I didn't realize
there were so many

297
00:15:08,666 --> 00:15:11,041
and such
a wide variety of types.

298
00:15:11,125 --> 00:15:14,000
That's especially true
in the Shinjuku prefecture.

299
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:17,416
What's more, I've never met
a human quite like you before.

300
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:19,000
You're unique.

301
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:21,375
It's a big world
out there, isn't it?

302
00:15:22,583 --> 00:15:25,083
Is that triggering
a memory for you?

303
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:27,000
No, not really.

304
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:28,916
But it does feel like
something is trying

305
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,416
to break through the fog.

306
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,083
[ARATA]
That's great.

307
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:35,875
Be sure to tell me the second
you notice anything at all.

308
00:15:35,958 --> 00:15:37,250
It could be important.

309
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:38,958
I'll be sure to do that,

310
00:15:39,041 --> 00:15:40,500
but first I have a request.

311
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:41,791
I haven't eaten yet.

312
00:15:41,875 --> 00:15:43,583
And after
all that chaos back there,

313
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:45,041
I'm feeling a bit hungry.

314
00:15:45,125 --> 00:15:47,125
Surely you must
be getting hungry, too?

315
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:48,375
I'll make something for us

316
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:49,833
as soon as we get back
to my place.

317
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:53,416
Actually, I just bought
some really nice honey.

318
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,375
It's imported,
supposed to be delicious.

319
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:57,291
[ANOTHER]
I can't wait to try that!

320
00:15:57,375 --> 00:15:59,250
♪

321
00:16:04,166 --> 00:16:05,333
[ARATA]
Okay, moment of truth.

322
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:07,291
[grunts]

323
00:16:07,375 --> 00:16:09,958
[sniffs]
Ah!

324
00:16:10,041 --> 00:16:12,291
-What's wrong?
-N-n-nothing.

325
00:16:12,375 --> 00:16:14,333
I'm fine.
That smells good.

326
00:16:14,416 --> 00:16:15,458
See what you think.

327
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,541
Thank you very much!

328
00:16:17,625 --> 00:16:20,000
♪

329
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,375
I, I think I might be familiar
with this particular honey.

330
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:29,166
-Huh?
-The rich beauty of its color,

331
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:30,458
like fine jewels.

332
00:16:30,541 --> 00:16:32,750
It glitters in the light
like dew on leaves

333
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:34,375
changing color in autumn.

334
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:37,000
And the sweet scent tickles
the heart with joy.

335
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:39,083
I remember it well!

336
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,583
♪

337
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:42,916
[gasps]

338
00:16:44,083 --> 00:16:47,083
-[birds chirping]
-[grass rustling]

339
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:49,833
♪

340
00:16:49,916 --> 00:16:51,875
[bees buzzing]

341
00:16:53,416 --> 00:16:56,375
♪

342
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:02,333
[swallows audibly]

343
00:17:04,583 --> 00:17:05,833
This is the one.

344
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:08,791
I have received many offerings
of this honey

345
00:17:08,875 --> 00:17:10,791
from people in need of my help.

346
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:12,333
They would offer it
with their prayers

347
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,750
for things like peace
for their families

348
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,625
and healthy cattle
or for a fertile harvest.

349
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:19,250
Yes, of course!

350
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:21,375
This honey is from my homeland!

351
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,666
[ARATA]
The Ukraine?

352
00:17:28,458 --> 00:17:30,625
[beeping]

353
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:32,458
[THEO]
Yep, that's it!

354
00:17:32,541 --> 00:17:34,791
This says he's an Another
called Volos!

355
00:17:34,875 --> 00:17:36,541
According to Slavic myths
from the region

356
00:17:36,625 --> 00:17:37,708
that's now the Ukraine,

357
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:39,666
he's the god of forests
and hunting.

358
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:42,875
He's also said to protect cattle
in the form of a bear.

359
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:45,375
Which explains
why he never tried to kill you

360
00:17:45,458 --> 00:17:46,541
when you were with him.

361
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:47,958
And that element of his story

362
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:49,791
helped me narrow down
his identity.

363
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:52,500
-How's it goin'?
-[GROUP] Uh...

364
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:54,166
Hey! We solved the mystery.

365
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:55,625
Oh!

366
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:57,125
Great, well, I guess
you won't be needing

367
00:17:57,208 --> 00:17:58,166
this thing, then.

368
00:17:58,250 --> 00:17:59,875
Needing what thing?

369
00:17:59,958 --> 00:18:00,833
Well.

370
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:03,541
[ARATA]
What is this?

371
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:05,500
I thought maybe
he'd see something there

372
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:06,958
that triggered a memory.

373
00:18:07,041 --> 00:18:08,666
But since you've
figured out who he is,

374
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,291
guess you don't need the help.

375
00:18:10,375 --> 00:18:12,333
You can still go if you want.

376
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:14,083
It's over in Ueno.

377
00:18:15,083 --> 00:18:17,208
[VOLOS gasps]

378
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:22,541
This is... This is it!
I have no doubt!

379
00:18:22,625 --> 00:18:26,041
At last, I've found
a new vessel and a new body!

380
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:29,458
[ARATA]
Huh?

381
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:35,500
[VOLOS] Tell me,
what will happen

382
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:37,041
to this statue after this?

383
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:38,458
[ARATA]
Huh?

384
00:18:38,541 --> 00:18:39,708
Let me see.

385
00:18:39,791 --> 00:18:41,583
It's a traveling exhibit,

386
00:18:41,666 --> 00:18:43,958
so it will either be sent back
to its home museum

387
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:45,416
or continue to travel the world

388
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:48,083
making appearances
like this one.

389
00:18:48,166 --> 00:18:50,000
[VOLOS]
Traveling the world?

390
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:53,625
Seeing places I've never visited
or even heard of before?

391
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:59,125
I've seen many things lately,
just over the past few days.

392
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:01,500
And if I'm allowed
to continue on that journey,

393
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:03,875
I will consider myself
very lucky.

394
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:09,250
♪

395
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:12,083
[VOLOS] The gods need
human emotions to survive.

396
00:19:12,166 --> 00:19:17,625
Like faith, gratitude, sadness,
along with their prayers.

397
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:19,333
I'd been forgotten,

398
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:21,791
and that caused my power
to be taken from me.

399
00:19:22,791 --> 00:19:25,916
If not for you, I would have
spent eternity spiritually dead.

400
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,250
The passion and loyalty
of your heart

401
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,833
are what saved my soul.

402
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:30,916
Thank you for that.

403
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,916
It's nothing. But sure.

404
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,875
All part of the job, Volos.

405
00:19:35,958 --> 00:19:37,125
Understood.

406
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:39,375
I hope you're proud
of this noble job.

407
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:40,375
I'm grateful.

408
00:19:40,458 --> 00:19:43,666
♪

409
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:46,541
[VOLOS] I just realized that
you never told me your name.

410
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:47,666
-Uh?
-[VOLOS] What is it?

411
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:51,250
Arata. Arata Miyako.

412
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:53,750
Hmm. That's a good name.

413
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,166
[engine starts]

414
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:58,166
♪

415
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:08,333
And I am Volos,
god of the Rus!

416
00:20:08,416 --> 00:20:12,541
Let the world's people know
that I, my name, and my power

417
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:15,583
have returned to rule
the forest once again!

418
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:18,333
Thank you, Arata Miyako!

419
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:22,083
[chuckles]

420
00:20:28,375 --> 00:20:29,250
[sighs]

421
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:30,708
[YUKI]
Arata!

422
00:20:30,791 --> 00:20:31,958
Uh. Huh?

423
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:33,875
Huh?

424
00:20:33,958 --> 00:20:35,583
[screams, grunts]

425
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:36,666
[YUKI]
I'm here!

426
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:39,958
Hi, Yuki!
Glad you're back!

427
00:20:40,041 --> 00:20:41,708
Missed you.

428
00:20:41,791 --> 00:20:44,583
I'm so glad that bear-smelling
guy found a place to go.

429
00:20:44,666 --> 00:20:46,541
I guess this means
you're back, too.

430
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:49,083
Wow. You look a bit weak.

431
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:51,083
That's what you get
when you take on those types.

432
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,750
[YUKI]
Are you okay, Arata?

433
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:54,083
[ARATA]
I'm just fine.

434
00:20:54,166 --> 00:20:56,541
It's all part of the job,
you know?

435
00:20:56,625 --> 00:20:59,583
Great. Let's go do
something fun now.

436
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:01,041
We could go look
at cherry blossoms?

437
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:03,333
No, I gotta head back
to the office.

438
00:21:03,416 --> 00:21:05,083
[YUKI] Okay! Then I'll wait
for you at home!

439
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:07,416
Ready to go?

440
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,708
[KOHAKU]
But I just got here!

441
00:21:10,291 --> 00:21:12,000
Hey! If you don't want
to see cherry blossoms,

442
00:21:12,083 --> 00:21:13,375
why don't we go fishing?

443
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:14,916
[ARATA]
Some other time, sure.

444
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,625
[scoffs] You're no fun!
I've got an idea!

445
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:20,458
I'll just come with you to work
and be your assistant!

446
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:22,375
[ARATA]
Nope! No, you will not.

447
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:24,625
♪

448
00:21:28,541 --> 00:21:32,458
[ARATA]
Yokai, angels, devils,

449
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:35,666
most of the occult creatures
you've read about, actually.

450
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:38,583
We have a name for them
for all the non-human creatures

451
00:21:38,666 --> 00:21:41,000
we come across
in our line of work.

452
00:21:41,083 --> 00:21:42,333
"Anothers."

453
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:46,125
-[rustles]
-Huh?

454
00:21:49,583 --> 00:21:52,833
[ARATA] Our job is to maintain
relations with the Anothers.

455
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:55,916
That way, if they start
causing problems for civilians,

456
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,833
we know exactly
how to take care of it.

457
00:21:58,833 --> 00:22:01,500
We are the Nocturnal Community
Relations Division

458
00:22:01,583 --> 00:22:03,583
working at the
Shinjuku Ward Office.

459
00:22:03,666 --> 00:22:07,208
And we take our jobs
very seriously.

460
00:22:07,291 --> 00:22:10,000
♪

461
00:22:10,083 --> 00:22:10,958
Uh?

462
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:13,291
Good morning, team!

463
00:22:13,375 --> 00:22:14,875
♪

